{"title_page": "1974\u201375 Washington Bullets season", "text_new": "{{NBA_season\n| team = Washington Bullets\n| end_year = 1975\n| DivisionWin = yes\n| ConferenceWin = yes\n| wins = 60\n| losses = 22\n| division = Central\n| division_place = 1\n| conf_place = 2\n| coach = [[K. C. Jones]]\n| arena = [[Capital Centre]]\n| television = [[WDCA]]\n| radio = [[WFED|WTOP]]\n| playoffs = [[1975 NBA Finals|NBA Finals]]<br><small>(Eliminated 0\u20134)</small>\n| bbr_team = WSB\n| prev_name = Capital Bullets\n}}\nThe '''1974\u201375 Washington Bullets''' played in their 14th season and 2nd in the Washington, D.C. area. The franchise changed their name from the Capital Bullets to the Washington Bullets. The franchise captured its 6th division title in 7 years by posting a franchise best record of 60\u201322.<ref name=\"Washington Wizards 1963-Present\">[http://www.sportsecyclopedia.com/nba/dc/wizards.html Washington Wizards (1963\u2013Present)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The Bullets were nearly unbeatable at home posting a record of 36\u20135 at the Capital Centre.<ref name=\"Washington Wizards 1963-Present\"/>  The Bullets won their second Eastern Conference title, but were swept in the [[1975 NBA Finals|NBA Finals]] in four games by the [[Golden State Warriors]].\n\n==Draft picks==\n{{main article|1974 NBA Draft}}\n\n==Roster==\n{{NBA roster header|team=Washington Bullets\n| bg1 = #C9143A | color1 = white\n| bg2 = #0344AD | color2 = white\n}}\n<!-- begin player list -->\n{{player2 | num = 45 | first = Phil | last = Chenier | pos = G | ft = 6 | in = 3 | lbs = 180 | college = California}}\n{{player2 | num = 23 | first = Dennis | last = DuVal | pos = G | ft = 6 | in = 3 | lbs = 175 | college = Syracuse}}\n{{player2 | num = 21 | first = Dick | last = Gibbs | dab = basketball | pos = F/G | ft = 6 | in = 5 | lbs = 210 | college = UTEP}}\n{{player2 | num = 11 | first = Elvin | last = Hayes | pos = C | ft = 6 | in = 9 | lbs = 235 | college = Houston}}\n{{player2 | num = 22 | first = Tom | last = Kozelko | pos = PF | ft = 6 | in = 8 | lbs = 220 | college = Toledo}}\n{{player2 | num = 10 | first = Kevin | last = Porter | pos = PG | ft = 6 | in = 0 | lbs = 170 | college = [[Saint Francis Red Flash men's basketball|Saint Francis (PA)]]}}\n{{player2 | num = 6 | first = Mike | last = Riordan | pos = SG | ft = 6 | in = 4 | lbs = 200 | college = Providence}}\n{{ player2 | num = 33 | first = Leonard | last = Robinson | dab = basketball | pos = F | ft = 6 | in = 7 | lbs = 225 | college = [[Tennessee State University|Tennessee State]]}}\n{{player2 | num = 41 | first = Wes | last = Unseld | pos = F | ft = 6 | in = 7 | lbs = 245 | college = Louisville}}\n{{player2 | num = 12 | first = Nick | last = Weatherspoon | pos = F | ft = 6 | in = 7 | lbs = 197 | college = Illinois}}\n<!-- end player list -->\n{{NBA roster footer\n| head_coach = \n*[[K. C. Jones]]\n| asst_coach =\n}}\n\n==Regular season==\n\n===Season standings===\n{{1974\u201375 NBA Central standings|team=WSB}}\n{{1974\u201375 NBA East standings|team=WSB}}\n'''Notes'''\n*'''z''', '''y''' \u2013 division champions\n*'''x''' \u2013 clinched playoff spot\n\n===Record vs. opponents===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=19|1974\u201375 NBA Records\n|-\n!width=100|Team\n!style=\"background:#FF0000;color:#FFFFFF;width=35\"|ATL\n!style=\"background:#006400;color:#FFFFFF;width=35\"|BOS\n!style=\"background:#000000;color:#F15110;width=35\"|BUF\n!style=\"background:#FF0000;color:#000000;width=35\"|CHI\n!style=\"background:#FFD700;color:#8B0000;width=35\"|CLE\n!style=\"background:#0000FF;color:#FF0000;width=35\"|DET\n!style=\"background:#0000FF;color:#FFD700;width=35\"|GSW\n!style=\"background:#FF0000;color:#FFD700;width=35\"|HOU\n!style=\"background:#0000FF;color:#FFFFFF;width=35\"|KCO\n!style=\"background:#800080;color:#FFD700;width=35\"|LAL\n!style=\"background:#006400;color:#B22222;width=35\"|MIL\n!style=\"background:#36004A;color:#FFFF00;width=35\"|NO